<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/1068: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-26T17:00:00-05:00">February 26, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>25. My 22, February 25, 6 p.m. The final minor changes we wanted were
                            made yesterday by the House on motion of the Minister of Industries and
                            the bill passed in second debate.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>